 :tx/rationale "DESIGN: Session Retrospective Protocol — self-calibrating guidance. At session end, compare recommended actions (R(t) output per turn) vs actual actions (transaction log). Guidance accuracy = |recommended ∩ actual| / |actual|. When accuracy < 50%, the routing weights are demonstrably miscalibrated. Resolution: record (recommended, actual, accuracy) as :retrospective/* datoms. Over 5+ sessions, fit a session_boost parameter from retrospective data — same single-parameter calibration pattern as KEFF-4. This is C7 self-bootstrap applied to the GUIDANCE layer: the system's routing improves from its own usage history. FORMAL PROPERTY: The retrospective forms a contraction mapping on routing error — each calibration cycle reduces |recommended - actual| divergence. Convergence guaranteed when session_boost is bounded. TRACES TO: C7, INV-GUIDANCE-010, SEED.md §7."
